sentences.sentence:
29 The amended statement of claim asserts the following:

• That the respondent has intentionally engaged in a series of activities that have resulted in Antarctic minke whales and fin whales being killed, taken and interfered with, and humpback whales being taken and interfered with, within the Australian Whale Sanctuary, and subsequently intentionally treated and possessed in contravention of ss 229, 229A, 229B, 229C, 229D and 230 of the EPBC Act;

• That the conduct was done in accordance with the Japanese Whaling Research Program under Special Permit in the Antarctic (JARPA) issued by the government of Japan under Article VIII of the Whaling Convention;

• That JARPA is not a recognised foreign authority for the purposes of subsection 7(1) of the Antarctic Treaty (Environment Protection) Act 1980 (Cth).
